         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">24/6/94. ¶  ¶ I owe you still an answer to your letter, received some few weeks ago, ¶  dear Mr Hart, but now in the quietness of the Sunday, while bringing up some arrear correspondence, I come also ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">94.06.24</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Thomas Hart</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M24, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">24/6/94.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I owe you still an answer to your letter, received some few weeks ago,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See T. Hart to M, 11 April 1894.</p>
               </note> dear Mr Hart, but now in the quietness of the Sunday, while bringing up some arrear correspondence, I come also to your Pterostylis for examining it closely. It is a form of P. reflexa, in the limitation of the species, as adopted for the Fl. Australiensis.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham (1863-78), vol. 6, p. 359.</p>
               </note> The leaves are smaller, than usual, indeed bract like. If more than one species become comprehended under the name P. reflexa, then the absolute limits of the specific forms have not yet been pointed out. Let me hope, that your prospects are brightening, and that your health is firm.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The Campaspe<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Campapspe River, Vic.</p>
               </note> locality is new for P. P.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter repeated in going from one line to the next.</p>
               </note> reflexa, and will be recorded under your honored name. By all means continue searches for rare plants including aquatics.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Pterostylis%20reflexa">Pterostylis reflexa</name>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
